Package core

Interface HlaDynamicalEntityManager

  • public interface HlaDynamicalEntityManager
    Manager used to manage HlaDynamicalEntitys.

    This class is ThreadSafe as defined by Java Concurrency in Practice, see jcip.net.

      • addHlaDynamicalEntityDefaultInstanceListener

        void addHlaDynamicalEntityDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaDynamicalEntityListener listener)
        Add a listener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaDynamicalEntity (Both local and remote). The listener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaDynamicalEntity is updated. The listener is also called when an interaction is sent to an instance of HlaDynamicalEntity. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to add.

      • removeHlaDynamicalEntityDefaultInstanceListener

        void removeHlaDynamicalEntityDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaDynamicalEntityListener listener)
        Remove a listener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaDynamicalEntity. Note: The listener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaDynamicalEntity. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to remove.

      • addHlaDynamicalEntityDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void addHlaDynamicalEntityDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaDynamicalEntityValueListener valueListener)
        Add a valueListener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaDynamicalEntity (Both local and remote). The Valuelistener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaDynamicalEntity is updated. Note that the attribute values that are notified are not guaranteed to be the latest available values for that attribute. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to add.

      • removeHlaDynamicalEntityDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void removeHlaDynamicalEntityDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaDynamicalEntityValueListener valueListener)
        Remove a valueListener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaDynamicalEntity. Note: The valueListener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaDynamicalEntity. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to remove.

      • setEnabled

        void setEnabled​(boolean enabled)
        Enables or disables the HlaDynamicalEntity manager. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaDynamicalEntity manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable the HlaDynamicalEntity manager, otherwise false

      • setEnabledIfAvailableInFom

        void setEnabledIfAvailableInFom()
        Enables the HlaDynamicalEntity manager if it is available in the FOM at runtime. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaDynamicalEntity manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Check if the HlaDynamicalEntity manager is actually enabled when connected. An HlaDynamicalEntity manager may be disabled with the setEnabled(false) function, or it may be configured as if available in the FOM by the setEnabledIfAvailableInFom() function and then not available in the FOM at runtime.

        This method should only be used when connected, it will always return false when not connected.

        Returns:
        true if connected and the HlaDynamicalEntity manager is enabled.
